{
  "act_id": "act_vertical",
  "title": "Vertical Motion Story",
  "viz_panel": "svg",
  "beats": [
    {
      "say": "Now for vertical motion — here gravity constantly pulls downward at 9.8 meters per second squared. Let's isolate the vertical component to see how it behaves.",
      "card": {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "Vertical motion is governed by constant downward acceleration due to gravity: $g = 9.8 \\text{ m/s}^2$"
      },
      "viz_actions": [
        {
          "method": "isolateMotion",
          "params": {
            "motionType": "vertical",
            "dimOpacity": 0.3
          },
          "offset": 0
        },
        {
          "method": "highlightComponent",
          "params": {
            "component": "vertical",
            "intensity": 1.2
          },
          "offset": "+0.5"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "say": "The vertical velocity starts at 20 meters per second upward, decreases due to gravity, becomes zero at the peak, then increases downward. Watch how the velocity vector changes direction.",
      "viz_actions": [
        {
          "method": "updateVelocityComponents",
          "params": {
            "time": 0,
            "showVectors": true
          },
          "offset": 0
        },
        {
          "method": "createMotionGraph",
          "params": {
            "type": "velocity",
            "axis": "vertical",
            "realTime": true
          },
          "offset": "+1.0"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "say": "Vertical position follows the kinematic equation: y equals v naught y times t minus one half g t squared. That's 20t minus 4.9t squared.",
      "card": {
        "type": "latex",
        "content": "y = v_{0y} \\cdot t - \\frac{1}{2}gt^2 = 20t - 4.9t^2",
        "highlight": true
      },
      "viz_actions": [
        {
          "method": "showEquation",
          "params": {
            "equation": "y = 20t - 4.9t²",
            "position": "top-right",
            "style": "physics"
          },
          "offset": 0
        },
        {
          "method": "markTimeInstant",
          "params": {
            "time": 2.04,
            "event": "peak",
            "color": "#f59e0b"
          },
          "offset": "+1.5"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "say": "Notice the beautiful symmetry — the upward journey mirrors the downward journey. The arrow takes the same time to rise as it does to fall.",
      "card": {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "Projectile motion is symmetric: time to reach maximum height equals time to fall back down."
      },
      "viz_actions": [
        {
          "method": "pulseObject",
          "params": {
            "objectId": "trajectory_peak",
            "intensity": 1.5,
            "duration": 1.0
          },
          "offset": 0
        },
        {
          "method": "markTimeInstant",
          "params": {
            "time": 4.08,
            "event": "landing",
            "color": "#818cf8"
          },
          "offset": "+1.0"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}